arStrings.szText: There. Oyuun? How do you feel?
Concerned but hopeful. She's just finished brewing a tea that she hopes will calm her traumatized companion.
What? Where? Oh... better, I think. (gasp) Yes. Oh, Zolaya, I'm so sorry. I don't know what came over me... (sigh) there was a smell and--and then... that place...
Confused. Coming out of a traumatic memory, gradually gaining her bearings back in the present moment. Then, ashamed and disgusted.
There's no need to apologize. I never expected you to be fine, after everything you went through. Now drink your tea. Rest.
Relieved. Dismissive in a light-hearted way (like "you silly girl"). In awe at how much her companion survived/endured.
(sigh) She seems to be calming down... for now. Once she's stabilized, I can go and collect more of those herbs. (sigh) Thank you.
Relieved. She sounds like she's carrying a large weight but is hopeful they're on the path to better things.
Wait! I have a favor to ask... my journals over there, will you take them with you? Please. Take them far away from here.
A bit disoriented, she calls out to the player as she realizes they're departing. Then referencing her journals, she's ashamed and disgusted.
